{"key":"processedPost-5954156","value":{"id":5954156,"first":5953691,"last":5959261,"when":1155331516,"utime":"08/12/06 12:25 AM","content":"Some of the biggest mushrooms I ever grew were on composted cow manure out of the bag.  Just mix it with coir and verm to fluff it up along with the straw, then add gypsum and pasteurize.  Most people aren't aware that cow/steer manure has more nitrogen content than horse manure.  We usually prefer horse manure simply because of the texture, because it's ready to use once field aged and dried.<br />RR","title":"Re: commercially available cow manure"}}